rComments: The worst professor in my academic career. Avoid taking her class if you have a German last name. My grades from her were 15-20% lower (in both of her classes) when compared to the other English classes I took taught by other professors... I'm an English Literature major - so I took a lot of other English classes. Save your GPA and avoid.
An outstanding, challenging, engaging and kind professor.

Dr. Goldman's grad seminar was excellent. Its challenge (weekly response papers) is also its benefit--I felt extremely inspired and engaged all term, and was well prepared for the end paper. Brilliant in private meetings--helpful and kind. Well spoken in class. A novel every two weeks, which really allowed for close reading. Great, great prof.
Smart, really funny, fair, respectful of students. Can't believe these people had the same prof. Maybe she's changed?
Had her the first year she started teaching - wasn't so bad, but got so mad when the half empty room filled up for a test!
Heinous beeyatch! Lectures were repetitive and boooring.
Worst experience of my academic career.
